  <respiratory_skin_sensitizer hazard_type="health">
    <hazard_name>Respiratory/skin sensitizer</hazard_name>
    <hazard_id>4.0</hazard_id>
    <classification>Respiratory sensitizer: Category 1 
Skin sensitizer: Category 1
</classification>
    <hazard_statement></hazard_statement>
    <rationale>Respiratory sensitizer: chromium is classified into "Respiratory Sensitizing Substance" by the ad hoc committee of the Japanese Society of Occupational Allergy, and "Respiratory Sensitizing Substance: Group 2"* by the Japan Society for Occupational Health. These classifications, though not specifying chromic chloride, seem to include chromium compounds. Chromic chloride, which is a chromium compound, should thus cause respiratory sensitization. 

Skin sensitizer: chromium is classified into "Skin Sensitizing Substance" by the ad hoc committee of the Japanese Society of Occupational Allergy, and "Skin Sensitizing Substance: Group 1"* by the Japan Society for Occupational Health. These classifications, though not specifying chromic chloride, seem to include chromium compounds. Chromic chloride, which is a chromium compound, should thus cause skin sensitization. 

* There is a provision to the effect that "the category refers to the substance concerned and its compounds, but does not identify all substances causing respiratory/skin sensitization.</rationale>
    <signal_word></signal_word>
    <symbol></symbol>
  </respiratory_skin_sensitizer>
